<body>
<div class="wrap">

  <header>
    <h1>Arda Başarıcı</h1>
    <p class="tag">Math + 3&nbsp;yrs game dev → AI/ML engineering.</p>
    <p class="tax">A bias for honest evaluation over shiny demos. Building a portfolio in public.</p>
    <div class="links">
      <a href="https://github.com/arda-basarici">GitHub</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ardabasarici">LinkedIn</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <hr>

  <h2>Projects</h2>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Betting Against the Noise</h3>
    <p>Can an RL agent rediscover Kelly bet-sizing on blackjack&rsquo;s thin, countable edge? A DQN
       bettor vs. the analytic Kelly ladder, measured four ways. The answer is no &mdash; and a
       rigorous account of exactly why (a signal buried fifty-deep in per-hand noise).</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/blackjack-betting">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/blackjack-rl-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>From Table to Network</h3>
    <p>Tabular Monte-Carlo vs. a DQN for blackjack play &mdash; what neural generalization repairs in
       coverage-starved cells, and what it distorts in return.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/table-to-network">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/blackjack-rl-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>The Policy Audit</h3>
    <p>Can tabular Monte-Carlo control rediscover blackjack&rsquo;s proven-optimal strategy table from
       win/loss alone? It recovers ~93% &mdash; and forcing coverage of rare states collapses the
       genuine disagreements 30 &rarr; 9, all near-ties: the residual was the cost of experience, not
       the method.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/policy-audit">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/blackjack-rl-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>pathfinding-ml</h3>
    <p>A learned A* heuristic, honestly evaluated: a Simpson&rsquo;s-paradox pooling trap, a
       regime-tag feature, and two opposite failures under distribution shift &mdash; measured on two
       axes never collapsed into one score.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/pathfinding">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/pathfinding-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Steam Review Intelligence</h3>
    <p>298k reviews across 50 games and 30 languages; four findings, each validated
       <em>within-group</em> rather than pooled. A pandas / pandera / Parquet data pipeline.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/steam-reviews">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/steam-reviews-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h3>Monte Carlo Blackjack Simulator</h3>
    <p>A configurable ~80M-hand engine with pluggable strategies and card counting &mdash; the
       measurement instrument the blackjack RL work is built on.</p>
    <div class="row">
      <a href="/blackjack-sim">Report (PDF)</a>
      <a href="/blackjack-sim-code">Code</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>
    <p>This page and the <code>/&lt;project&gt;</code> redirect files are the single place to update
      links when repositories move &mdash; published posts and PDFs point here, not at deep repo paths.</p>
  </footer>

